    "history" -> {"12", "14.0", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"linear algebra", "vector space"}, "specialkeywords" -> {},
     "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "Ket[{b1, b2, ..., bn}] represents a computational basis state Ket[{b1, \
b2, ..., bn}] on a register of n unlabeled quantum systems (usually qubits). \
For a single system, Ket[b] with integer v is an alias to Ket[{b}] for \
convenience. Ket[{s1 -> b1, s2 -> b2, ...}] represents a computational basis \
state Ket[{b1, b2, ...}] on a register of labeled quantum systems s1, s2, \
.... Ket[spec, {s1, s2, ...}] or Ket[spec, s] is equivalent to \
KetRegulate[Ket[spec], {s1, s2, ...}]] or KetRegulate[Ket[spec], {s}]. This \
is useful to specify input/output states in QuantumCircuit. Ket[<|...|>][s1, \
s2, ...] returns a list of the values associated with the Species s1, s2, \
....", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "Ket", "titlemodifier" -> 
    "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> "Ket", "type" -> "Symbol", 
    "uri" -> "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/Ket"}},
